        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2435094597" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15612734014862765621">Lots of thoughts and thoughts and more thoughts about the very beginning and very end of a 30 year marriage. Way too much head space without any action and a failure to get the reader emotionally involved with the characters. We know the unlikable characters will get together and that Margaret will die in the end. There is too much repetition with the point that the main character dropped out of school to write a novel and that Margaret has blue eyes. <br/>Reading about the author it seems as this no</span>
  <span id="freeText15612734014862765621" style="display:none">Lots of thoughts and thoughts and more thoughts about the very beginning and very end of a 30 year marriage. Way too much head space without any action and a failure to get the reader emotionally involved with the characters. We know the unlikable characters will get together and that Margaret will die in the end. There is too much repetition with the point that the main character dropped out of school to write a novel and that Margaret has blue eyes. <br />Reading about the author it seems as this novel is quite biographical and must have been healing to write. However it is much too long with Enrique's thoughts without much of any plot. Luckily the novel is well written so it is fluid enough to read through.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15612734014862765621" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

