<div id="review_622897741" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/622897741" />
    <a title="Erika Nerdypants" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5708431-erika-nerdypants"><img alt="Erika Nerdypants" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1527871103p2/5708431.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/622897741?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erika Nerdypants" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erika Nerdypants" href="/user/show/5708431-erika-nerdypants">Erika Nerdypants</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5708431-erika-nerdypants?shelf=grieving">grieving</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5708431-erika-nerdypants?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5708431-erika-nerdypants?shelf=2013-reading-challenge">2013-reading-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer622897741" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10244342889568801569">SPOILER ALERT<br/>I had a love-hate relationship with this book. The story of Enrique&apos;s marriage, beginning with courtship and ending with the death of his wife Margaret from invasive cancer. I loved the gritty, honest writing of the chapters that dealt with Margaret&apos;s illness and her final days. I quickly grew tired and then loathed the parts that described the early courtship, during which, pardon the pun, Enrique couldn&apos;t rise to the occasion. Did I really need a whole chapter of mostly Enrique&apos;s </span>
  <span id="freeText10244342889568801569" style="display:none">SPOILER ALERT<br />I had a love-hate relationship with this book. The story of Enrique's marriage, beginning with courtship and ending with the death of his wife Margaret from invasive cancer. I loved the gritty, honest writing of the chapters that dealt with Margaret's illness and her final days. I quickly grew tired and then loathed the parts that described the early courtship, during which, pardon the pun, Enrique couldn't rise to the occasion. Did I really need a whole chapter of mostly Enrique's inner dialogue as he is trying to work up the nerve to kiss Margaret? I don't mind reading books with protagonists I don't really like. But Enrique truly tried my patience. Self-involved, dishonest, callous about his wife's feelings, he only redeemed himself somewhat by taking care of her, and finally placing her needs above his selfish wants. Still didn't make him terribly likable however. And because Enrique eclipses Margaret's story, we don't find out what her perspective on this marriage was. With autobiographical novels, which this seems to be, it's too hard to discern fact from fiction to really say, "this is what happened". The final chapters which contain brutally honest descriptions from a deathbed struggle are beautifully written, but were completely spoiled for me by alternating paragraphs in which we are given a blow by blow description of Enrique finally succeeding in making love to Margaret. As Margaret is slipping out of this world, in the parallel story, Enrique is ejaculating. That did nothing for me, and I don't consider myself prude. Didn't love it, but also have to say that the parts I did like, I liked very much. Bewildering.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10244342889568801569" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

