<div id="review_106131119" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/106131119" />
    <a title="Irene" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1110606-irene"><img alt="Irene" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1316182619p2/1110606.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/106131119?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Irene" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Irene" href="/user/show/1110606-irene">Irene</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1110606-irene?shelf=2010">2010</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer106131119" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17789196132364780720">Yet another story about a smug, artsy, sensitive man who doesn&apos;t appreciate his wife and the life/love/family they created until she is either about to leave him or die on him, or both.<br/><br/>I&apos;m not generalizing here when I say that sometimes men have their heads up their asses. Especially when they write about how they miss their beloved dead wives after having conducted a prolonged affair with said wives&apos; close friend, after having thought that the love was gone because said wives didn&apos;t feel like f</span>
  <span id="freeText17789196132364780720" style="display:none">Yet another story about a smug, artsy, sensitive man who doesn't appreciate his wife and the life/love/family they created until she is either about to leave him or die on him, or both.<br /><br />I'm not generalizing here when I say that sometimes men have their heads up their asses. Especially when they write about how they miss their beloved dead wives after having conducted a prolonged affair with said wives' close friend, after having thought that the love was gone because said wives didn't feel like fellating them more than once a month after birthing a child, etc.<br /><br />Really really really childish and immature. Are we supposed to think you're suddenly a saint because you nursed her when her cancer ate her from the inside out? And just say it's ok that you were doing her best friend for a year and was about to leave her for the best friend and then decided against it because of a small fit of fear? <br /><br />Somehow, Mr. Yglesias, I think you admire your Mr. Enrique Sabas, because he turned into a fine, mature man for caring for a terminally ill wife. Umm. I don't think so.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17789196132364780720" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


